Instruction: With the good 12 V battery in place, use a continuity tester (power off if required) to check each path inside the PSU: (1) from battery positive terminal to the positive output cable, (2) from battery negative terminal to the negative output cable, and (3) from battery positive to the anode of the green LED and from LED cathode back to battery negative. Identify whether there is an open circuit in either main output lead or in the LED branch.
